rComments: I took this class in fall 2020, when all classes were online. Although the classes were pre-recorded, they were very interesting. He has a way to make every session interesting no matter the subject. I don't know how his classes are in person, but if they are as good as the online ones, you won't be disappointed.

His lectures were all pre-recorded with no slides at all, just his voice. it was a bit difficult to take notes at times, but overall it was alright. despite the long lectures, they were still very interesting. Even with the most complex subject, he explains it well. If you take time to listen the lectures carefully, you wont have any problems.
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures ', 'Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: He's ok. Has office hours and helps students but the projects are terrible. 40% on a resume... which most of us have never done in philosphy (because, contrary to the POL title this IS A PHILO CLASS), really? No TAs to talk to and the prof will not give you good feedback just « ok » and « okay ».. how am I supposed to do better next time?
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Lots of homework', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Personally I had audio recordings which took a godly amount of time to listen too so slides would have been better for sure. But he seemed like such a nice guy and he truly cares and wants the best for his students and he is really engaging when he speaks and is passionate. I would definitely take him again :).
Super boring lectures with no PowerPoints and very difficult readings. I wouldn't recommend him if you're a French Immersion student, although his lectures are pretty slow so not hard to understand.
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: So the pros of having monsieur couture online is that you get to have access to all go the recordings and the material. Also, all of his exams are home exams. The cons are that the material itself is heavy and you will need to find time and pull many all-nighters and Do a ton of research in order to hand in one simple paper of 3 pages.
teacherRatingTags: ['Test heavy', 'Get ready to read', 'So many papers']

rComments: Horrible teacher and assignments.

Does not use slideshows, and chose to make his online class entirely audio recordings. This was a huge barrier for french immersion students since every lecture was like a listening exam. It once took me 3 hours to listen to a 1-hour lecture since I kept rewinding. Had a weird grade distribution, 40% for a single summary, mid-term + final worth 30%
teacherRatingTags: ['Graded by few things', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: His online lectures are a nightmare. He never even showed his face and only communicated by discussion group once before each assignment. If you are a visual learner, avoid his class at all cost. There are no live lectures or powerpoint slides.

Tough grader, leaves unnecessary comments on papers. Wishing he would've been more understandable with his grading criterias, especially when his classes are audios to listen to asynchronously (VERY hard for note taking).

les notes ont été données via une note vocale d'une heure. super chiant. Il est très difficile à atteindre et ne communique avec la classe que par chat toutes les 3 semaines. Les manuels n'étaient que des textes de Socrate et Platon et de tous ceux qui étaient pertinents à l'époque. J'aurais aimé que nous puissions écrire ses notes vocales à la pla

literally if you take couture ur asking for it. Maybe its because of Covid but he was so difficult to deal with, was very rude and unreasonable. His marking is unfair and doesn't provide proper comments. Doesn't have PowerPoints, just audio recorded lectures. Good luck

The lectures were very good, but information was given quickly and there wasn't any slides or information posted online, which meant I got most of my information from the course readings. He gives out the exam questions in class, and then randomly selects two to be answered on the final exam, so you know exactly what to study.

i regret taking this class. mans doesnt use or upload powerpoints for lectures and since french is my second language, i struggled with note taking. really wish i could go back in time and change my schedule so i never have to take this class

Va vous faire adorer la philo. Humour sarcastique mais pas méchant. Pas de powerpoint. Si vous manquez un cours, vous devez absolument demander les notes de quelqu'un d'autre, sinon vous aurez de la difficulté à l'exam. Un recueil de texte et un livre à lire (pour travail de session). Travaillez fort.

This was one of the best classes I took. Not only is he a hilarious prof but is very close to his students, he does not have powerpoints but writes on the board so you would want to attend class to take notes. The discussions are interesting so is the book. Very interesting class and even better prof.

He just speaks and expects you to record everything. He's also quite unapproachable and rude. French is my second language and when I went to speak to him he corrected my accent multiple times for trivial words, it was pretty discouraging and stopped me from speaking to him again.

Phenomenal prof. Definitely knows his stuff, especially on Greek mythology and whatnot. Always available by email to answer your questions. If he feels as if the TA's grade too low, he does fix your grade. Gives out exams questions early. Super nice, interesting lectures. Only downside, no notes on brightspace at all. Great guy tho.

Excellent prof. Ces cours sont extrêmement intéressant et stimulant. Le seul problème est qu'il donne aucun note de cours donc il faut non seulement se présenter à tous les cours mais être très attentif à ce qu'il dit. Ces travaux sont parfois difficile mais il est juste et offre beaucoup d'aide.

Very good prof. I always look forward to the lectures (even the 8:30 ones)! He's a very good speaker - engaging, enthusiastic and tries to get the class involved. Unfortunately, there are no class notes available online or a textbook - so you pretty much have to go to lectures and try to catch everything he says. Gives out the exam questions early.

Ce prof etait excellent! La matiere n'est pas super interessante mais le prof reussit vrmt a la simplifier! Il n'est pas tres severe et est toujours ouvert a des differents point de vue. Il n'y a pas de test, juste des mini papiers. Excellent!
Excellent professeur. Je l'ai eu pour POL2507 également et j'ai adoré. Explications claires, articulées et précises. Très aidant et toujours humoristique.

Hands down the best prof at the university. He's clear, helpful and funny. He knows what he's talking about and he's very inspiring. Yes, there are lots of readings and assignments, but if you give an effort, you will get a good grade.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Un des meilleurs, sinon le meilleur professeur que j'ai eu à date à l'université. Professeur très clair et intelligent. Il transmet bien la matière et ses cours sont très intéressants! Il est très marrant et stimule la classe avec son humour! Excellent cours de pensée politique.
Excellent prof! Il faut travailler fort pour une bonne note, mais ses attentes et sa matière sont très claires.
Excellent prof. Je le recommanderais. Il est exigeant et tu dois travailler pour avoir une bonne note. Cependant, il transmet très bien la matière de manière claire et concise.

Meilleur cours que j'ai déjà eu! Un prof très clair, concis et motivant. Ce qui le rend encore plus charmant c'est son humour dérisoire et ses remarques toujours cyniques. Très bien organisé et prepare bien ses cours. Sans usage de diapos et ses lectures suggerées sont très pointues. Y aller est un vrai plaisir pour l'esprit et les yeux!

Very interesting prof ! His lectures are always prepared and easy to understand. He's really helpful and he's always available during his office hours. There's a lot of reading, but it pertinent for the course.
Meilleur cours de la session. Ce prof est clair et concis et parvient toujours à insérer une remarque dérisoire toujours pleine d'humour cynique. Très bien organisé. Merveilleux prof.

Well first off, he's a good looking prof. Very smart, very knowledgeable.Went to see him a few times for a resume we had to hand in,was very helpful in that. Just a bit nevervous for the final as he's giving us 7q to prepare and he picks 2 to answer in the final.Overall, you work hard, and go seehim for anything you arent sure of and you'll b fine
This teacher is awesome! He makes the subject so interesting and is really funny. Extremely helpful and always answers e-mails quickly. Overall great experience, I recommend this prof !
teacher is a marxist, this is apparent in his teachings. He is also a hard grader. He is very clear in his teachings, and is a very nice man

Il est l'un des meilleurs professeurs que j'ai eu, même si parfois il est un peu snobe! Il est très stimulant, drôle et garde l'intérêt des étudiants sans diaporama mais seulement en parlant et en interagissant avec la classe. Il y a plusieurs lectures obligatoires mais elles sont tous sur Campus Virtuel. Il y a très peu d'évaluation dans le cours!

Meilleur prof de ma session étudiante jusqu'à date.  M. Couture est super bien organisé, ses cours son clairs et intéressants, et il est extremement marrant et intelligent.  Ne prenez pas ce cours avec un autre prof que lui!

Très bon prof! Il explique la matière de manière très claire et concise. Rend la pensée politique un sujet intéressant et tente souvent à faire rire les étudiants avec ses blagues sur Platon et Aristote. Toutefois, il faudra travailler fort parce qu'il n'avait que 2 fiches, un resume de 40% et un examen final.
Awesome prof.  Loved the class, loved listening to him talk.  Also, totally hot.

Good Class. No text book but lots of readings to print off. No midterm exam. Final exam is based purely off of lectures and the readings. He doesn't post or use powerpoints so attending class is pretty mandatory.

Son enseignement est stimulant. Il a les bonnes techniques pour enseigner. Ses évaluations sont à revoir, car elles sont peu nombreuses mais très pondérées. En général, excellent cours et excellent prof!
Excellent prof.  Bons examples, bonnes manières de présenter les concepts et de faires ses évaluations.
Best prof ever! Requires work, but is so clear and SO interesting
Le professeur souhaite la reussite de tous. Il defend lexcellence des cours universitaires. Ce pourquoi il est severe.,
Vraiment excellent professeur, très vif d'esprit, avec un humour intelligent.  Il est passionné, et ça paraît.  Le cours est facile si on fait ce qu'on a à faire et qu'on y met un peu d'effort.
very pernickety
Good Class!
Hard marker, but great teacher.
good prof, good class. He's young so he can relate to students.

Great teacher. Clear, concise. Great topics discussed in class. Interesting projects. Obviously has a lot of knowledge, invested interested in teaching students and funny to boot. I would definitely recommend this class.
Jean-Pierrrrrrrrrrre! tu es un super chouette prof-en!Tu es hy-per tendance-en et très styliiiiish-en, t'inquiète-en mec-en, t'as tout pour faire d'une classse-en, une super boîte disco-trash-en.
connait tres bien sa matiere il est jeune, agreable et amusant, il sait transmettre la philosophie de facon plus facile a analyser. bravo. meme si tres strict

Derrière son look dictateur et ses manières stoïques, il sait se montrer humain et empathique aux besoins des elèves. Il detruit vite les a priori negatifs des premiers cours à son egard et montre une bonne connaissance de sa maitère. Il est souple dans les corrections ... OK en general
